  "doc_id": "30316",
  "text": "The resistive inductive (RL) shunted circuit technique is generally accepted for passive vibration damping control of a single mode or multi-modes (Ref. [CITATION_1] ). However, a major problem with this approach is the large inductor size and mass for low frequency-tuned resonant circuit. Consequently, many researchers proposed the use of synthetic inductors (Refs. 10 and 11) to reduce the weight and volume of the circuits. It required a constant power supply, and its size was still considerably large.",
  "correct_citation": {
